        <title>Agent Choice via Quantum Flux in Living Systems</title>
            <categories>quant-ph physics.bio-ph</categories>
            <license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license>
            <abstract>A basic model is provided that places active, intentional choices by biological organisms on a solid physical footing. The model is provisionally called &#34;Agent Choice via Quantum Flux.&#34; It brings to bear specific physics on living systems in a way that allows for intentional choices not pre-determined by physical laws, but remaining consistent with those laws. It does so by exploring a possible many-to-one relation of quantum states to agent choices, with a parallel to the relation of thermodynamic microstates to macrostates.</abstract>
